Since junixsocket 2.4 (although you should use the latest version, currently 2.5.2), we support &quot;casting&quot; `FileDescriptor` to several other objects, such as `Socket`, `InputStream`, etc.

junixsocket will make sure that the &quot;cast&quot; (which isn&#39;t a trivial cast since it returns another object) succeeds  as long as the conversion is valid.

Example:

    FileDescriptor fd = ...;
    AFUNIXSocket socket = FileDescriptorCast.using(fd).as(AFUNIXSocket.class);

More details here: https://kohlschutter.github.io/junixsocket/filedescriptors.html

